Introduction

Park Gyeong-bok, also known as Park Seoham, is a South Korean singer, actor, and model under NPIO Entertainment. He is best known for being a member of the boy group KNK and starring in the BL web drama "Semantic Error."

Seoham started his journey as a trainee under Big Hit Entertainment, training alongside fellow member Inseong and BTS. After parting ways with Big Hit, Seoham was admitted to JYP Entertainment as an actor trainee after winning second place at the agency's 2013 Open Auditions.

After years of training, Seoham ended up debuting as a member of the boy group KNK on March 3, 2016 under 220 Entertainment. In September 2021, he left the group and agency to pursue his acting career elsewhere.

In 2022, Seoham garnered local and international interest after starring in the BL drama "Semantic Error" alongside DKZ's Jaechan. Not long after, he signed with the agency NPIO Entertainment. On March 10, just 3 days after joining the agency, Seoham announced through a heartfelt letter that he would be enlisting for his mandatory military service.
